Definition: act in unison or agreement and in secret towards a deceitful or illegal purpose
Example: The two companies conspired to cause the value of the stock to fall
Synonyms: adj, pert, conspirative, noun, communication, conspiracy, collude, all, covert, collusive, collusion, cognition, verb, social, interact, act, in, unison, or, agreement, and, secret, towards, a, deceitful, illegal, purpose, The, two, companies, conspired, to, cause, the, value, of, stock, fall
Frame: 1,2,28
Category: verb.cognition
